<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
If going thru an overland-grass type zone, I have a small risk of being ambushed where I'm surrounded by some trees and can't get out! Not to mention the case where I can reach the border but everything on the border I can reach is a tree despite the fact it's a grass zone on the other side(with some trees present on some squares)... <p>
Ambush status should be removed after 1 day of game time, to avoid all such situations. 
</p>
<p>
Seen in 2.2.2 once and 2.3 once after considerably frequent trips while level 3 or less. (-; 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NerdanelVampire">NerdanelVampire</a>: I feel your pain. I have had similar experiences in Annals of Ea with quest entrances that were situated on a mountain square... 
</p>
<p>
Always carry some sort of digger with you to avoid such situations in the future. Trees are easy to get through or over after all. You can't say the same about hard rock, particularly when you are playing a dragon with no slot for a climbing set... 
</p>
<p>
If I don't have a digger after hitting a trap that adds some walls, that's my fault and I do deserve to die. But for most other stuck situations (notably the fact nearby walls can't be digged after I load the game) a but fix would be better... 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: This is known, but the parchment you start the game with TELLS you to get a digger, doesn't it?  I'm inclined to call this more bad luck than a bug. 
</p>
<p>
Simon: somehow it was illogical to use a shovel to cut trees. It took a stretch of the imagination to see their roots unearthed and trees falling over in one round(with a pick, I wouldn't have imagined it possible). But after 4 deaths I did finally tried it. I expected the digger advice to be for dungeons, NOT the wilderness... 
</p>
<p>
Anyhow. My dig wand won't work on trees. After a loaded-saved game so my trees are undiggeable and some are invisible(I'll wait for day and see what happens). I'll even activated a non-*ID* junkart who put me exactly where I started... I wonder what that is, maybe an unlucky teleport? 
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


